# Creating GUIs with PySimpleGUI

User mannual at https://www.pysimplegui.org/en/latest/

An abstraction layer on top of (or wrapper around)
Tkinter, wxPython and PyQt. (Resently also HTML related Remi.)
Don't have to use classes to create user interfaces.

pip install pysimplegui

See: hello.py
and  hello1.py

Supported elements:
https://pysimplegui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/#element-and-function-call-reference
Creating multiple windows:
https://pysimplegui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/#running-multiple-windows

Two design patterns...


